@adriancole there is the [Profile API](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/search-profile.html), which I would try first.

There is also the [graphical profiler](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/kibana/6.0/xpack-profiler.html) based on that API. That one is in X-Pack Basic, so you will need to install X-Pack into Elasticsearch and Kibana and then you can either use the 30 day trial or get the [free basic license](http://register.elastic.co) for extended periods.
Would be interesting to see the graphical breakdown where you are spending your time and then you could start digging further how / where to improve.

@gianarb noticed this crashes when browser language is italian. There's probably an easy fix for that but.. wonder if we shouldn't crowd-source some more languages?

@shakuzen japanese?
@gianarb italian?
@marcingrzejszczak polish?
@dsyer english? (hehe)

@adriancole, @fedj, any progress made on dealing with clock skew when spans come from different hosts? Even when using ntpd, the clocks are very close, but evidently not close enough:

![clock-skew](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/879507/33861854-cfcf60c6-de94-11e7-8c0f-a529d6b039a0.png)

What's the best way to deal with this when deploying distributed tracing?
